quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,35,"And he went in unto his garden, having thus wronged himself: said he, \"I do not think that all this will ever perish"
  18,36,"And I think not that the Hour (of Judgment) will ever come; and even if I be sent back unto my Lord, I shall surely find something even better in exchange"
  18,37,"His neighbour, while he disputed with him, exclaimed, \"Disbelieve you in Him who created you from dust, and then from a drop, then fashioned you into a man"
  18,38,"But He is Allah, my Lord; and I associate no partner with my Lord"
  18,39,"Why could you not have said when you did enter into your garden, ´As Allah pleases! (Or It is Allah´s will or Allah´s will always comes to pass). There is no power save in Allah!´. Though you see me as less than you in wealth"
  18,40,"It may be that my Lord will give me something better than your garden, and will send upon it a bolt from heaven, and it shall be but bare slippery mud on the morrow"
  18,41,Or some morning the water thereof will be deeply sunk in the earth so that you can not get thereat
  18,42,"And his fruits were beset (with ruin). Then began he to wring his hands for all that he had spent thereon, for now it had crumbled down to its foundations. And he said, \"Would that I had ascribed no partner with my Lord"
  18,43,"And he had no troop of men to help him against Allah, nor could he save himself"
  18,44,"In such a case the patronage is Allah´s alone, the True; He is best at rewarding and best for consequences (or success)"
  18,45,"Strike out for them, also, a similitude of the life of this world; like water, which We send down from the sky, and the vegetation of the earth absorbs it; but on the morrow (or soon) it is dried up, and the winds scatter it; for Allah is powerful over al"